{"type":"message","id":"75d9d811","parentId":"3989aa58","timestamp":"2026-03-17T08:28:01.207Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Task Completion Summary\n\nI've successfully executed the OpenClaw document update checking script task. Here's what I accomplished:\n\n1. **Analyzed and fixed the existing scripts**:\n   - Found issues with the original `docs_update_agent.js` script\n   - Added necessary Node.js module imports\n   - Fixed the update summary handling\n\n2. **Created improved scripts**:\n   - `send_docs_update.js`: A simplified update notification script\n   - `docs_update_summary.js`: An improved analysis script that filters out HTML metadata changes\n   - `check_and_notify_docs_update.sh`: A comprehensive wrapper script for easy execution\n\n3. **Added documentation**:\n   - Created a README.md with system overview\n   - Added detailed usage instructions in UPDATE_DOCS_HOWTO.md\n\n4. **Tested the system**:\n   - Verified that the document checking works\n   - Confirmed that update summaries are properly analyzed and formatted\n   - Ensured that non-substantive changes (HTML metadata) are identified as such\n\nThe system now successfully:\n1. Checks for updates in OpenClaw documentation\n2. Distinguishes between meaningful content changes and irrelevant HTML metadata changes\n3. Generates clear, formatted update notifications\n4. Maintains proper backup versions of all documents\n5. Provides comprehensive logs for troubleshooting\n\nThe scripts are ready to be used manually or scheduled via cron for automatic monitoring of OpenClaw documentation updates."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"anthropic/claude-3.7-sonnet","usage":{"input":1253,"output":333,"cacheRead":39872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41458,"cost":{"input":0.003759,"output":0.004995,"cacheRead":0.0119616,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0207156}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773736073373}}
